headlines.headline: Joseph hits go-ahead single in 9th, Orioles beat Blue Jays
headlines.description: Caleb Joseph singled home the go-ahead run with two outs in the ninth inning and the Baltimore Orioles beat the Blue Jays 5-3 Saturday, ending Toronto's home winning streak at nine games.

headlines.headline: Rodon, White Sox end 8-game skid, beat Rangers 3-2
headlines.description: Carlos Rodon pitched six effective innings and the Chicago White Sox snapped a season-worst eight-game losing streak, beating the Texas Rangers 3-2 on Saturday.

headlines.headline: Castro lifts Cubs past Twins in 10 innings
headlines.description: Starlin Castro atoned for a costly error the previous night with a two-run single in the in the 10th inning on Saturday, helping the Chicago Cubs to a 4-1 victory over the Minnesota Twins.

headlines.headline: Hahn wins third straight, A's beat Angels 4-1
headlines.description: Jesse Hahn pitched into the eighth inning for his third consecutive win, Josh Reddick hit a tiebreaking double in the sixth and the Oakland Athletics beat the Los Angeles Angels 4-1 on Saturday a

headlines.headline: Max Scherzer loses perfect game with HBP in 9th but completes no-hitter
headlines.description: Max Scherzer pitched a no-hitter Saturday, losing his perfect game with two outs in the ninth inning when he hit a batter in the Washington Nationals' 6-0 win over the Pittsburgh Pirates.

headlines.headline: Blackmon's 3 RBIs lead Rockies past Brewers 5-1
headlines.description: Charlie Blackmon homered and drove in three runs, Chad Bettis pitched effectively into the seventh inning and the Colorado Rockies snapped a five-game losing streak with a 5-1 victory over the Mi

headlines.headline: Grichuk's 2 homers, Lackey's pitching lead Cards past Phils
headlines.description: Randal Grichuk hit two home runs, doubled and drove in four runs, and John Lackey pitched seven strong innings to lead the St. Louis Cardinals to a 10-1 victory over the Philadelphia Phillies on

headlines.headline: Longoria homers to lead Rays past Indians 4-1
headlines.description: Evan Longoria hit a three-run homer in the first inning and the Tampa Bay Rays handed reigning Cy Young winner Corey Kluber his fourth straight loss with a 4-1 victory over the Cleveland Indians

headlines.headline: Morales homers on birthday in Royals' 7-4 win over Red Sox
headlines.description: Kendrys Morales homered on his 32nd birthday and the Kansas City Royals rallied to beat the Boston Red Sox 7-4 on Saturday night.

headlines.headline: Simmons has 4 hits, Braves beat Mets as d'Arnaud injured
headlines.description: Andrelton Simmons got four hits for the Atlanta Braves in a 6-4 win Saturday night over the New York Mets 6-4, who lost their fourth in a row and catcher Travis d'Arnaud to an elbow injury.

headlines.headline: Nicolino sparkles in debut as Marlins beat Reds 5-0
headlines.description: Left-hander Justin Nicolino pitched seven innings to win his major league debut and Derek Dietrich hit two home runs as the Miami Marlins snapped a three-game losing streak with a 5-0 victory ove

headlines.headline: A-Rod gets 5 RBIs, Carlos Beltran homers from both sides of plate in rout
headlines.description: Alex Rodriguez added to his momentous weekend with a homer and five RBIs, Carlos Beltran went deep from both sides of the plate, and the New York Yankees routed the Detroit Tigers 14-3 Saturday.

headlines.headline: Maxwell, Belt power SF Giants past LA Dodgers yet again, 6-2
headlines.description: Justin Maxwell and Brandon Belt hit two-run homers and the San Francisco Giants trimmed the Dodgers' NL West lead to a half-game with a 6-2 victory over Los Angeles on Saturday.

headlines.headline: Walker fans 11, Mariners power past Astros 6-3
headlines.description: Taijuan Walker struck out a career-high 11 while pitching into the seventh inning to lead the Seattle Mariners to a 6-3 win against the Houston Astros on Saturday night.

headlines.headline: Ross throws 4-hitter, Padres rout Diamondbacks 8-1
headlines.description: Tyson Ross threw a four-hitter in his third career complete game and the San Diego Padres beat the Arizona Diamondbacks 8-1 on Saturday night.
